<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1579] Cloned SegmentReaders fail to share FieldCache entries</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1579</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I just hit this on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1516&quot; title=&quot;Integrate IndexReader with IndexWriter &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUCENE-1516&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1516&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which returns a cloned readOnly&lt;br/&gt;
readers from IndexWriter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is, when cloning, we create a new &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;thin&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; cloned&lt;br/&gt;
SegmentReader for each segment.  FieldCache keys directly off this&lt;br/&gt;
object, so if you clone the reader and do a search that requires the&lt;br/&gt;
FieldCache (eg, sorting) then that first search is always very slow&lt;br/&gt;
because every single segment is reloading the FieldCache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is of course a complete showstopper for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1516&quot; title=&quot;Integrate IndexReader with IndexWriter &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUCENE-1516&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1516&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-831&quot; title=&quot;Complete overhaul of FieldCache API/Implementation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUCENE-831&quot;&gt;LUCENE-831&lt;/a&gt; we&apos;ll switch to a new FieldCache API; we should ensure&lt;br/&gt;
this bug is not present there.  We should also fix the bug in the&lt;br/&gt;
current FieldCache API since for 2.9, users may hit this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
